      "side": 1,
      "message": "My remaining concern here is that the instances of `struct pldm_package_format_pin` represent the extensible _C_ structs, which are distinct from the extensible C++ structs. The value is related to but also separate from the spec\u0027ed package format revisions, so I don\u0027t think it\u0027s appropriate to mix them in this way. I\u0027d rather develop equivalent pins for the C++ API so it can evolve independently of the C API (even if it\u0027s implemented in terms of the C API).",
